I LOVE that we have so many cool adventure opportunities on this planet, and I want YOU to join me and #crushit4climate this month! This is a fun reminder to enjoy our amazing outdoors while learning what we can do to keep them clean. 
🤩
Here’s the deal - every week in my bio I’ll be linking an article relating to climate change. This first week’s article is by Kendra Pierre-Louis, “For a Climate Reporter, a dreaded question: ‘then why is it so cold?’” and your giveaway prize is a $100 gift certificate to @llbean AND a pair of @oakley Sutro Lite glasses. 😎
Winner will be randomly chosen and notified by DM, so check your messages! Each week will have a new article to read and a new winner, so have fun and keep crushing it!

node.text:
You didn’t think I’d forget to give you a new core challenge for July, did you?!? 
Here it is:
1. Boat pose with right leg extended, left leg, then both legs
2. Leg lowers with weight held overhead - the farther back you hold it, the harder it gets!
3. Roll-ups that are slow and controlled, especially on the way down
4. Leg lowers at an angle to each side 

Start with body weight, working your way up to holding a plate over your head - and if you’re feeling crazy, use a slosh tube (like me in the video) for the extra challenge of weight that unpredictably moves! Try 30 seconds of each exercise. 💪🏼

Come train with us! ⚡️ While I’d love to be able to come run a workout with every team that reaches out, I can’t drive up and down the East coast all summer. But…you can come visit us in Stratton! We are opening up select workouts to anyone who wants to join us. All ages and abilities welcome! This is a great chance to ask questions, meet the team and do intervals with some of the best skiers in the world! It’s also free, so, you know, that’s kinda nice. 😉

Tomorrow at 8:30am (Saturday July 10th) meet us at the base of the Stratton Mountain Gondola for a ski walk interval session up the mountain! Bring shoes, water and short poles (if you have them)!

Next week on Wednesday July 14th, we are hosting an open skate roller ski clinic from 3-4pm in Stratton Sun Bowl. Come ski with us, do some drills and have fun with agility! 

Saturday July 17th at 9am we are doing a long run from the Mad Tom Notch parking lot for a loop around Griffith lake, Peru and Styles peaks. 
We will hang out at Hapgood pond for a swim and picnic lunch (bring your own) after! 
📷: Matt Whitcomb

IG vs reality…but in reverse? Swipe right to see what was happening just out of frame during Monday’s lift with Sports Illustrated. 👉🏼👀 Honestly, this was a great test of focus for me! This is a year of finding balance; of acknowledging pressure and expectations without being consumed by them. Of going all out because it’s what I love to do, not because of who’s watching, or who isn’t. That said…thank you @sifullframe for showing how we go all out and #liftlikeagirl 💪🏼
📷: @jcorkski

Excited to share that @salomon is unveiling their new sustainability goals, and a plan for going forward with our environmental impact in mind!
🌎
Starting in 2022, Salomon is pledging to offset the global carbon footprint of the entire international athlete team! 🙌🏼 They’re also going to work with all of us to help us learn how to lessen our individual impacts. This really hits home for me, as I travel a lot for ski racing and I’m the first to say that I’m an imperfect advocate - which doesn’t mean we should give up, stop trying, or stop learning. I’m humbled and inspired by Salomon’s efforts and excited to continue to grow in this area! 
🙏🏼
I’m so, so proud to be part of a team that looks forward and is taking steps to ensure we have an amazing planet to play on in the future! Check out the link in my bio and head to @salomon to learn more about these initiatives! #PlayMinded #salomon 

 📷: Pete O’Brien
